{%- comment -%} 2. Start here — three steps {%- endcomment -%}
<section class="section bg-white" id="SmartGuide--{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Starting from nothing? Three steps.</h2>
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
      <div class="shg-step"><h3 class="shg-step-h"><span class="shg-num">1</span> Pick one room</h3><p>Do not plan the whole house. Buy smart bulbs for one room, live with them for a week, and you will know what you actually want next. Almost nobody gets the plan right on paper.</p></div>
      <div class="shg-step"><h3 class="shg-step-h"><span class="shg-num">2</span> Buy bulbs before switches</h3><p>Smart bulbs screw into your existing fittings and need no wiring. Smart wall switches replace the switch and need a qualified electrician. Start with bulbs.</p></div>
      <div class="shg-step"><h3 class="shg-step-h"><span class="shg-num">3</span> Add a speaker when you want voice</h3><p>An Echo or a Google Home is not required. Your lights work from their app without one. Add it when you want voice control, or when you want devices from different brands running in the same routine.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

