{%- comment -%} 4. The one rule {%- endcomment -%}
<section class="section bg-white">
  <div class="container shg-narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">The one rule that explains everything</h2>
    <div class="lsq-prose" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <p>Brands do not join each other's hubs. A Wink bulb will not pair with a Philips Hue Bridge. A Yeelight will not join the Mi hub. Those are closed systems and they are meant to be.</p>
      <p>But every brand here connects to Alexa and Google Home. So a Wink bulb, a Yeelight strip and a Xiaomi plug can all sit in the same voice command and the same routine, even though none of them can see each other directly. The assistant is the meeting point, not the hub. Once you understand that, mixing brands stops being a problem.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

