{%- comment -%} 8. FAQ — answers in the initial HTML, collapsed {%- endcomment -%}
<section class="section bg-white" id="SmartFAQ--{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title text-center">Smart home questions, answered</h2>
    <div class="faq-wrap">
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Do I need a hub for smart lighting? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>For most of what we stock, no. Wink, Xiaomi, Yeelight and Sonoff devices connect straight to your home WiFi and run from their app. Philips Hue is the exception: Hue bulbs include Bluetooth so you can start with a few lights without one, but the full range and the best performance need the Hue Bridge.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Can I mix smart brands in one home? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>Yes, through Alexa or Google Home. What does not work is adding one brand's device to another brand's hub: a Wink bulb will not join the Hue Bridge, and a Yeelight will not join the Mi hub. But all of them connect to Alexa and Google Home, so you can control them together by voice and in the same routines.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Do I need to rewire to make my lights smart? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>No, not to start. Smart bulbs screw into your existing fittings and connect over WiFi. Rewiring only comes in if you choose smart wall switches, which replace the existing switch and should be fitted by a qualified electrician. Damage from installation not carried out by a qualified electrician is not covered.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Which app do I need? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>It depends on the brand. Wink uses Tuya or Smart Life, Sonoff uses eWeLink, Xiaomi uses Mi Home, Yeelight uses the Yeelight app with many products also in Mi Home, and Philips Hue uses the Hue app. Most can then be linked into Alexa or Google Home so you control everything from one place by voice.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Do smart lights work if my internet goes down? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>The switch on the wall still works, so you will not be left in the dark. App and voice control need the internet, and cloud-based routines pause until the connection returns.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Can I control my lights from outside Qatar? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>Yes. These are WiFi devices connected through their app, so you can switch lights and change schedules from anywhere with an internet connection.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>What should I buy first? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>Smart bulbs for one room. They need no wiring, they work from the app without a speaker, and after a week you will know whether you want strips, switches or voice control next. Almost nobody plans a smart home correctly on paper.</p></div></div>
      <div class="collapsible-row"><h3 class="collapsible-trigger-h"><button class="collapsible-trigger" type="button" data-accordion>Will smart bulbs work with my existing dimmer switch? <span class="material-symbols-outlined">expand_more</span></button></h3><div class="collapsible-content"><p>No, and this is worth knowing before you buy. A smart bulb does its own dimming from the app, so it needs constant mains power. On a dimmer switch it will flicker, buzz or fail early. Either replace the dimmer with a normal switch and dim from the app, or use a smart dimmer switch designed for it. Ask our team if you are unsure.</p></div></div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-center" style="margin-top:1.5rem;"><a class="btn-outline" href="{{ wa }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ask us on WhatsApp</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

